summary: how i got into loving taylor and my journey til now.
body:
how i got into loving taylor and my journey til now.

it all started when i was in england. i was sitting on our little red couch and i saw we are never ever getting back together on the TV. i had heard the song before probably on the radio or something but i didn’t know that i would be hooked on taylor for the rest of my life. i remember getting up and dancing to the song. seven year old me in my pjs dancing to WANEGBT. then after that day i downloaded everything thing has changed, WANEGBT and IKYWT on my ipod. i remember at one point WANEGBT was the only song that was on my ipod but i listened to that one song on repeat. also i would go in the car with my grandparents and listen to everything has changed and look out the window like i was in a movie.

as soon as i got to australia i got more and more obsessed over taylor. i remember 8 year old me, running to the boot of the car because i had just heard the news that mum had bought me my very first album “red”. that album is now very broken because i listened to it non stop. i remember dancing around my room thinking i was taylor and getting really puffed out. i once took it to school and some guy took it and dropped it in a puddle. which i cried about but it still works. but it’s very cracked.

since i didn’t have the money to buy the rest of taylor’s albums i went on youtube and listened to her songs. then as soon as i got a new album i would listen to it non stop so i would learn all the words. i remember since i was used to taylor’s country music when shake it off came out. i hated it. i thought what is this? i was obviously regretted it after the second time listened to it because i was dancing to it and singing it. and then i counted down the days until 1989 came out and i was so so sooo excited to listen to it. then reputation came out and of course i listened to it non stop.

the rep tour was my first time ever seeing taylor. and i was so so soooo excited. i could not stop talking about it. and i counted down the days from 100. at that point i didn’t know i was going until day 53 i came home from school and my mum suprised me saying that i was going. i cried and cried. i was so happy. the day of rep tour was so so exciting and i miss it so much. as soon as i saw taylor on stage even if she was tiny made me cry. the person that i had listened to for most of my life was right infront of me.

so here i am now. waiting for ts7. and i can’t wait for it.

and @taylorswift i love you so so so so much. and that will never change in 131313131313131313131313131 years.

💓💓💓💓💓💓💓💓💓💓💓💓

summary: i'm not the type of person to talk about sadness and bad stuff because i'm a happy person. but sometimes i feel like no one...
body:
i’m not the type of person to talk about sadness and bad stuff because i’m a happy person. but sometimes i feel like no one cares about me. no one wants to be around me. that i’m a weird music nerd that talks about taylor all the time so no one listens to me. but taylor makes me feel like i matter. she makes me feel like i’m worth every single thing in the world. that at the end of the day i don’t feel good that i know that there will always be one person that loves me and cares about me. taylor makes me feel this way.

i want to thank her one day. face to face. but i know that it will never happen. i’ve been wishing it for 7 years and it’s not come true. i want to tell her how much i love her and appreciate what she does. i want to give her the biggest cuddle ever and explain to her that she is my best friend. and i love her with all my heart and that will never ever ever change in a million years. 💓

@taylorswift @taylornation
